The paper deals with the problem of multi-view face detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of machine learning techniques such as MLPs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of shape-indexed features, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper deals with the issue of time-cost, which is a concern in computer security (cs.CR) as well.
